Title: Marky - Image Restoration Business support tool

Marky - Image Restoration Business support tool
===============================================


The project dependencies
=========================

Production dependencies
-----------------------
- mysql
- Apache2 mod_xsendfile (http://tn123.ath.cx/mod_xsendfile/)
- RMagick (image processing). See [install](#rm_install) for Ubuntu.
- Paperclip: better install from source *script/plugin install git://github.com/thoughtbot/paperclip.git*




Development dependencies
------------------------
- maruku gem (documentation generation from Markdown)
- ZenTest (for autotest)
- autotest-notification
- autotest-rails



RMagick Installation {#rm_install}
-----------------------------
*Installation*

Ubuntu 9.10 Packages (install via apt-get):
 - imagemagick - image manipulation programs
 - librmagick-ruby - ImageMagick API for Ruby
 - libmagickwand-dev - image manipulation library - development files



*gem installation:*

    james@karmic:~$ sudo gem install rmagick
    Building native extensions.  This could take a while...
    Successfully installed rmagick-2.12.2
    1 gem installed
    Installing ri documentation for rmagick-2.12.2...
    Updating class cache with 2777 classes...
    Installing RDoc documentation for rmagick-2.12.2...

*Testing*
Open an irb session and try the following

    require 'RMagick'
    #=> true
    require 'rvg/rvg'
    #=> true
    include Magick
    #=> Object



